    "description": {
      "value": "<p><strong data-start=\"373\" data-end=\"415\">Scrapper’s Cunning (Passive; Bloodied)</strong><br data-start=\"415\" data-end=\"418\" />You thrive in desperate conditions.</p><p data-start=\"455\" data-end=\"561\">While you are <strong data-start=\"469\" data-end=\"481\">bloodied</strong> (at or below <strong data-start=\"495\" data-end=\"526\">half your hit point maximum</strong>), you gain the following benefits:</p><ul data-start=\"563\" data-end=\"806\"><li data-start=\"563\" data-end=\"654\"><p data-start=\"565\" data-end=\"654\">You have <strong data-start=\"574\" data-end=\"587\">advantage</strong> on <strong data-start=\"591\" data-end=\"615\">Strength (Athletics)</strong> and <strong data-start=\"620\" data-end=\"646\">Dexterity (Acrobatics)</strong> checks.</p></li><li data-start=\"655\" data-end=\"806\"><p data-start=\"657\" data-end=\"806\"><strong data-start=\"657\" data-end=\"674\">Once per turn</strong>, when you hit with a <strong data-start=\"696\" data-end=\"712\">melee weapon</strong> or <strong data-start=\"716\" data-end=\"734\">natural weapon</strong> attack, you deal <strong data-start=\"752\" data-end=\"805\">additional damage equal to your proficiency bonus</strong>.</p></li></ul><p data-start=\"808\" data-end=\"857\">These benefits end if you are no longer bloodied.</p><hr data-start=\"859\" data-end=\"862\" /><h3 data-start=\"864\" data-end=\"899\"><strong data-start=\"868\" data-end=\"899\">Auspice Ribbon (Choose One)</strong></h3><ul data-start=\"900\" data-end=\"1438\"><li data-start=\"900\" data-end=\"993\"><p data-start=\"902\" data-end=\"993\"><strong data-start=\"902\" data-end=\"915\">Ragabash:</strong> While bloodied, opportunity attacks against you are made with disadvantage.</p></li><li data-start=\"994\" data-end=\"1090\"><p data-start=\"996\" data-end=\"1090\"><strong data-start=\"996\" data-end=\"1008\">Theurge:</strong> While bloodied, you have advantage on saving throws against poison and disease.</p></li><li data-start=\"1091\" data-end=\"1172\"><p data-start=\"1093\" data-end=\"1172\"><strong data-start=\"1093\" data-end=\"1106\">Philodox:</strong> While bloodied, you have advantage on contested ability checks.</p></li><li data-start=\"1173\" data-end=\"1306\"><p data-start=\"1175\" data-end=\"1306\"><strong data-start=\"1175\" data-end=\"1188\">Galliard:</strong> When you first become bloodied, one ally within 30 feet gains temporary hit points equal to your proficiency bonus.</p></li><li data-start=\"1307\" data-end=\"1438\"><p data-start=\"1309\" data-end=\"1438\"><strong data-start=\"1309\" data-end=\"1320\">Ahroun:</strong> While bloodied, once per turn you may reroll one damage die on a melee or natural weapon attack and use the new roll.</p></li></ul><hr data-start=\"1440\" data-end=\"1443\" /><p data-start=\"1445\" data-end=\"1504\"><br /><code data-start=\"1466\" data-end=\"1504\">[GAROU_FEATURE] id=scrappers-cunning</code></p>",
